Policemen attached to A Division in Warri, Delta State on routine stop-and-search duty at the front of Daudu police outpost, Pessu Community in Warri, have recovered one locally made cut-to-size pistol in a black handbag abandoned by suspected armed robbers. This was according to a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. According to DSP Edafe, the policeman on duty sighted a tricycle driving against traffic and attempted to stop it. “The suspects dangerously maneuver the tricycle and escaped, but in the process, a black handbag fell from the tricycle. Upon searching the bag, one locally made cut-to-size pistol was recovered,” he disclosed while assuring that efforts are ongoing to arrest the fleeing suspects.